args: Ha! It is the traitorous prince and his band\nmost foul! Mark me well: today's sunrise\nshall be the last you ever see!
Hell, that's a whole lotta goons.\nWe're gonna be boxed in at this rate.
Let's back off. There's no reason for us\nto fight when the odds are against us.
If you intend to leave with all of your\nlimbs attached, I suggest you carry out\nthat plan with all haste.
No idea, but I'm thinkin' it's the right call\nfor us to beat feet outta here!
Those logs divided the Empire's forces!
I'm guessin' it's the work of that voice\nfrom before. Regardless, I think it's\ngiven us a spark of new life!
Right. Time to strike back, everyone!
Is he the man who set off that log trap?
Whoever he is, he's on our side—\nso let's just focus on makin' these\nimperials take a long dirt nap!
Ran away, did they? Fine by me.\nThey can think long on the value\nof the lives they yet have left.
I assume those logs were your doing?\nThank you—we were in a real bind\nback there.
Hang on. VICTOR?! Is that you?!
Ah, Ranzal—the Arc in the Storm.\nI haven't seen you since that time\nyou were hired by Baron Djorden.
We fought together a couple'a times\nback in my old merc days.
But I heard your current band of\nmercenaries was annihilated, Victor.

Yeah, I heard it from a merc bud of mine.
Victor here was leadin' a band called the
Shadewolves what had an unfortunate
run-in with the Empire.

But there's darker rumors, too—like about
how the leader of the band won't die,
and now spends his nights huntin' down
imperials on some quest for revenge.
Rumors are just that, Arc: rumors.\nIt's not like you to fall for tall tales.
Yes, we sustained heavy losses at the\nEmpire's hand, but the Shadewolves\nhave not lost yet. The battle isn't over.
And what battle is that, exactly?\nYou against the whole damn Empire?

Alone or not, so long as I live on, so do
the Shadewolves—and I swear on the
honor of my comrades that I will carry
this fight to the ends of the earth.
Hmm. It seems we have a straggler.\nOne moment—this won't take long.
The Shadewolves whisper to me—and they\ntell me to leave no Empire servant alive.
And what was your answer when my\ncomrades asked the same of you?
Th-that wasn't me... I didn't touch 'em!
And yet you serve the Empire all the same,\nwhich means your life is forfeit.
What is this? I thought the Empire\nwas your enemy as well.
They are—but I still won't take an\nopponent's life when they are\nready and willing to surrender.
And what would you have me do with\nthis man, hmm? Bear in mind that he\ncame here specifically to take your lives.
I won't raise my sword against a helpless\nenemy. ...Soldier, gather those who can\nstill move and return to the Empire.
You didn't even take him prisoner...?\nHmm. It seems the rumors of your\nnature are true.
Fine, I will not interfere.\nNow, Prince, I have a proposal:\nI want you to hire the Shadewolves.
Ain't the Shadewolves just you now?
I may be alone, but my work—and the\nShadewolves' legacy—will speak for itself.
I've seen your strength. A powerful ally\nlike you is always welcome in our ranks.
But let me make something clear:\nWe are not seeking to take the life of\nevery imperial soldier we encounter.
I will not abide you attacking helpless\nenemies, or those who wish to surrender.
And if they only pretend to be helpless?\nWhat would you have me do then?
We'll just figure that out as a team\nwhenever we get to it.
That kind of responsibility is shared with\nall of us—not just given to one person.
If you agree to these terms, then you\nare welcome to fight at our side.
If those are my employer's wishes,\nI will abide them.
(Those who wish to flee may flee.\nBut in the end, I will destroy them all...)
